Melania and President Trump extend their warmest greetings to Jewish people celebrating Rosh Hashanah and the start of the High Holy Days. They acknowledge the significance of Rosh Hashanah as the beginning of the New Year in the Jewish faith, marked by the blowing of the shofar. They mention the practice of teshuva, or repentance, during the Ten Days of Repentance as a way to deepen one's relationship with God. The couple reflects on the importance of religious liberty and acknowledges the resilience of the Jewish people in overcoming persecution and suffering. They pray for God's peace, love, and mercy during the High Holy Days and wish a blessed and happy New Year to all those observing Rosh Hashanah.